The paper deals with object recognition in still images, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a biologically inspired model (HMAX), which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses modifications to the HMAX model to improve its computational efficiency, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the modified HMAX model on an FPGA, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
